Multi-Faceted Storm To Punch Through Southwest

March 5, 2025

Another potent storm will turn southward over the Southwest and Rockies with rain and snow later this week. Southern California could see localized flooding before the storm moves east. The southern-hanging storm will then bring wind gusts strong enough to cause a few power outages, enhanced fire concerns and dust storms from Arizona to west Texas. This storm will also likely bring some rain and thunderstorms into your weekend plans across the South. Here’s what you need to know.
